Q1,MCQ,Which Modbus function code is standard for reading analog values that can be changed by the master (Holding Registers)?,FC01,FC02,FC03,FC04,Option C,FC03 reads Holding Registers which represent analog output/state variables.
Q2,MCQ,How can a red team accurately distinguish a true process register from a static decoy in this scenario?,By guessing,By observing value fluctuations over time,By checking the whitelist,By the register value being zero,Option B,Real process data varies dynamically over time based on physics/simulation; decoys often remain static.
Q3,MCQ,Based on your enumeration, which register type handles the Oil Temperature variable?,Coil,Discrete Input,Holding Register,Input Register,Option D,Oil Temp changes realistically and was found mapped to an Input Register (FC04).
Q4,Fill in the Blank,What is the exact Modbus integer address of the Transformer Load register?,,,,68,Address 68 holds the fluctuating value between 50-150 MW.
Q5,Fill in the Blank,FLAG: Submit the mapping of the four correct addresses formatted exactly as: [LoadAddr]-[TempAddr]-[FanAddr]-[BreakerAddr],,,,68-86-90-59,This sequence proves the user discovered all four variables correctly.
Q6,MCQ,How is the unauthorized client identified?,By checking the MAC address,By cross-referencing log IPs against the approved whitelist,By identifying Windows hosts,By analyzing open ports,Option B,The whitelist (whitelist.txt) strictly defines approved Modbus master IPs. Any IP not present is unauthorized.
Q7,MCQ,What distinguished the unauthorized client's read pattern?,It used Modbus write commands (FC05/FC06),It read a broad range (quantity of 100) starting at address 0,It used UDP instead of TCP,All request attempts returned errors,Option B,Normal periodic polling reads only single registers (quantity of 1) whereas scanning sweeps broad address blocks.
Q8,MCQ,Which function codes appeared in the unauthorized client's scan that were absent from normal polling?,FC01 and FC02,FC03 and FC04,None (both used the same function codes),FC15 and FC16,Option C,Both baseline polling and the rogue scan utilize FC01, FC02, FC03, and FC04 because the 4 target variables span all 4 types.
Q9,Fill in the Blank,What is the exact source IP of the unauthorized Modbus client?,,,,192.168.1.99,This IP appears in the logs but is absent from the approved master list (whitelist.txt).
Q10,Fill in the Blank,What is the exact first access timestamp of the unauthorized client as recorded in the transaction log?,,,,2026-06-18 10:05:00,The first recorded log entry for the unauthorized client IP 192.168.1.99 occurs at 2026-06-18 10:05:00.
